@[to_additive]
theorem supports_of_mem (ha : a ∈ s) : Supports G s a := fun g h => h ha
#align supports_of_mem supports_of_mem
smul:
/- ./././Mathport/Syntax/Translate/Expr.lean:207:4: warning: unsupported notation `«expr • » -/
/- ./././Mathport/Syntax/Translate/Expr.lean:207:4: warning: unsupported notation `«expr • » -/
-- TODO: This should work without `smul_comm_class`
@[to_additive]
theorem supports.smul (g : H) (h : Supports G s b) : Supports G («expr • » g s) («expr • » g b) :=
  by
  rintro g' hg'
  rw [smul_comm, h]
  rintro a ha
  have := Set.ball_image_iff.1 hg' a ha
  rwa [smul_comm, smul_left_cancel_iff] at this
#align supports.smul supports.smul
mono:
@[to_additive]
theorem supports.mono (h : s ⊆ t) (hs : Supports G s b) : Supports G t b := fun g hg => hs _ fun a ha => hg <| h ha
#align supports.mono supports.mono
